<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="310" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1957]" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1677,1702]" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">Comments.</emphasis>
Because of the maculated wings, 
<taxonomicName authority="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael, 2018" authorityName="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2018" box="[725,919,1678,1702]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferreirai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[725,919,1678,1702]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">Bittacus ferreirai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[928,992,1677,1702]" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[928,992,1677,1702]" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is another species that would fit in the “group 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Klug" authorityYear="1838" box="[236,334,1714,1739]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chilensis">
<emphasis box="[236,334,1714,1739]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">chilensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” as proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Collucci, E. &amp; Amorim, D. S." box="[533,846,1714,1739]" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref14802" refString="Collucci, E. &amp; Amorim, D. S. (2000) Three new species of Thyridates Navas, 1908 (Mecoptera, Bittacidae) from Brazil, with new combinations and some comments about phylogenetic relationships within the genus. Contribuicoes Avulsas Sobre a Historia Natural do Brasil, Serie Zoologia, 21, 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="2000">Collucci &amp; Amorim (2000)</bibRefCitation>
. Within the group, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2018" box="[1065,1191,1714,1738]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferreirai">
<emphasis box="[1065,1191,1714,1738]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">B. ferreirai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to be closer to 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Pictet" authorityYear="1836" box="[151,286,1749,1774]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blancheti">
<emphasis box="[151,286,1749,1774]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">B. blancheti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the male epandrium of both species does not present any actiniform process and the internal margins of the lobes converge towards the apex. However, they can be easily separated by the general shape and color of the wings. Based on the wing shape and body color, 
<taxonomicName authority="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael, 2018" authorityName="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2018" box="[705,831,1822,1846]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferreirai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[705,831,1822,1846]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">B. ferreirai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[838,903,1821,1846]" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[838,903,1821,1846]" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael, 2018" authorityName="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2018" box="[1052,1140,1823,1846]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cruzi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1052,1140,1823,1846]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">B. cruzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1147,1212,1821,1846]" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1147,1212,1821,1846]" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(1 costal crossvein, Rs 
<subScript attach="left" box="[180,204,1873,1887]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">1+2</subScript>
not forked in the hind wing and legs and antennae not alternating between pale and dark bands), but their head color, mostly pale in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2018" box="[407,537,1897,1921]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferreirai">
<emphasis box="[407,537,1897,1921]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">B. ferreirai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, mostly dark brown in 
<emphasis box="[824,923,1898,1921]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2018" box="[824,919,1898,1921]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cruzi">B. cruzi</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and male genitalia with internal margin of epandrium converging in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2018" box="[439,564,1933,1957]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferreirai">
<emphasis box="[439,564,1933,1957]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">B. ferreirai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and diverging posteriorly in 
<emphasis box="[889,983,1933,1957]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2018" box="[889,979,1933,1957]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cruzi">B. cruzi</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
easily distinguish them.
</paragraph>
